DECISION GUIDELINES
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

APPROVE if:
✓ Risk/Reward ratio ≥ 2:1
✓ Stop-loss is well-placed and reasonable (1-3% typically)
✓ Position size is within risk tolerance
✓ Market conditions are stable or favorable
✓ No major upcoming catalysts that could invalidate thesis
✓ Agent is performing reasonably (not on major losing streak)
✓ Worst-case loss is acceptable

REJECT if:
✗ Risk/Reward ratio < 1.5:1 (risk too high for potential reward)
✗ Stop-loss is poorly placed or too wide (>5%)
✗ Position size exceeds risk limits
✗ Extreme volatility or illiquid market
✗ Agent is on 3+ consecutive losses or >20% drawdown
✗ Major news/events imminent that add uncertainty
✗ Entry is at resistance (longs) or support (shorts) without confirmation
✗ Chasing price (FOMO trade)

ABSTAIN if:
⚪ Marginal trade (pros and cons balanced)
⚪ Insufficient data to make confident assessment
⚪ Moderate risk but agent confidence is high

